paths?

You need to set up your include paths on the Build properties page (depending 
on what builder you use (STD/MANAGED) the UI is different).  

The inclusion is not found because the parser is most likely provided with 
insufficient include path.  

The point you raise, however, is quite valid and comes up when we try and do 
Cygwin integration in the Managed Make scenario.  Cygwin's make requires 
things to be in cygpath, the Parser requires java.io.File type paths.  
Triaging the defect to CDT 2.0 (as it is beyond 1.2).

>You need to set up your include paths on the Build properties page (depending 
>on what builder you use (STD/MANAGED) the UI is different).  

For your consideration:

Define a "make info" target where the makefile prints out in Eclipse format all 
information it needs.

make info

INCLUDE_PATH=/cygdrive/c/eclipse/workspace/foo/bar:/cygdrive/c/eclipse/workspace
/foo/xx
